Title: Multi-Purpose Agricultural Machine

Design Thinking for Social Innovation Project

Description:
As part of the Design Thinking for Social Innovation course, I worked on a project titled Multi-Purpose Agricultural Machine, aimed at improving farming efficiency through an innovative and cost-effective solution. The project focused on addressing real-world agricultural challenges by integrating multiple farming operations into a single machine.

Project Design & Functionality:
The proposed design fulfills essential farming needs by combining:

Plowing

Seed sowing

Fertilizer spraying

Weed removal

into one versatile and user-friendly system, making it accessible to small and medium-scale farmers.

Approach & Methodology:
The project followed a structured design thinking approach, which included:

User research to understand farmers‚Äô needs

Ideation and concept development

Prototyping and iterative testing

Refinement based on usability and practicality

Outcome & Impact:
The solution emphasized affordability, sustainability, and ease of operation, helping reduce labor, time, and equipment costs while enhancing productivity.

